{
  "page": "Hunchbacked septon",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/50px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/75px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/100px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Hunchbacked septon</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/50px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/75px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/100px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Hunchbacked septon by Mike S Miller.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/79/Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/350px-Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"293\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/79/Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/525px-Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/79/Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/700px-Hunchbacked_septon_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>The hunchbacked septon, illustrated by Mike S. Miller for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> <a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight_(comics)\" title=\"The Hedge Knight (comics)\">graphic novel</a>.</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Stoney_Sept\" title=\"Stoney Sept\">Stoney Sept</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>hunchbacked septon</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Stoney_Sept\" title=\"Stoney Sept\">Stoney Sept</a> living during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hunchbacked_septon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He had a hunchback.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hunchbacked_septon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a>, the septon preached in the market square of <a href=\"/index.php/Stoney_Sept\" title=\"Stoney Sept\">Stoney Sept</a> against Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodraven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloodraven\">Bloodraven</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> and half-uncle of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>, and in favor of the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackfyre_Pretenders\" title=\"Blackfyre Pretenders\">Blackfyre Pretenders</a>. For this <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a>, he was executed, and his head was displayed on an <a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a> spike above the town gates.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Egg\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Egg\">Egg</a>, were leaving Stoney Sept, they saw the head. Duncan thought the face looked familiar, and Egg reminded him they had seen the hunchbacked septon preaching three days earlier. Dunk recalled that Lord Bloodraven was accused of having various <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">sorcerous</a> animal spies, which he doubted, but it was certain that Bloodraven had informers everywhere. After they were a good distance from the town, Dunk argued it was a bad idea to cut off the head of a holy man, as words were merely words, but Egg pointed out the septon's words were treason and lies. Dunk rebutted that it still set a bad precedent, since fools and liars were everywhere.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later, when Dunk heard Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kyle_the_Cat\" title=\"Kyle the Cat\">Kyle the Cat</a> blaming Bloodraven for the troubles of the realm and saying that many would welcome the return of <a href=\"/index.php/Bittersteel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bittersteel\">Bittersteel</a>, he remembered the hunchbacked septon and warned Kyle that words like that could cost a man his head.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hunchbacked_septon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hunchbacked_septon%27s_head_by_Gary_Gianni.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Hunchbacked_septon%27s_head_by_Gary_Gianni.jpg/350px-Hunchbacked_septon%27s_head_by_Gary_Gianni.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"576\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/4/4c/Hunchbacked_septon%27s_head_by_Gary_Gianni.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hunchbacked_septon%27s_head_by_Gary_Gianni.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The hunchbacked septon's head, on the walls of <a href=\"/index.php/Stoney_Sept\" title=\"Stoney Sept\">Stoney Sept</a> after he was executed for <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a>. Illustrated by Gary Gianni for <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Knight_of_the_Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms\">A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms</a></i>.</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>His hands are scarlet with <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">a brother's</a> blood, and the blood of his <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aegon Blackfyre\">young</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aemon Blackfyre\">nephews</a> too. A <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow_assassin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shadow assassin\">shadow</a> came at his command to strangle brave Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Valarr_Targaryen\" title=\"Valarr Targaryen\">Valarr</a>'s sons in <a href=\"/index.php/Kiera_of_Tyrosh\" title=\"Kiera of Tyrosh\">their mother's</a> womb. Where is our Young Prince now? Where is his brother, sweet <a href=\"/index.php/Matarys_Targaryen\" title=\"Matarys Targaryen\">Matarys</a>? Where has Good King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron</a> gone, and fearless <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Breakspear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Baelor Breakspear\">Baelor Breakspear</a>? The grave has claimed them, every one, yet he endures, this pale bird with bloody beak who perches on King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys's</a> shoulder and caws into his ear. The mark of <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_hells\" title=\"Seven hells\">hell</a> is on his face and in his empty eye, and he has brought us drought and <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Spring_Sickness\" title=\"Great Spring Sickness\">pestilence</a> and murder. Rise up, I say, and remember our <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_II_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon II Blackfyre\">true king</a> across the water. <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Seven gods</a> there are, and <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_kingdoms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Seven kingdoms\">seven kingdoms</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">the Black Dragon</a> sired <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\">seven sons</a>! Rise up, my <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> and ladies. Rise up, you brave <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> and sturdy yeomen, and cast down <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodraven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloodraven\">Bloodraven</a>, that foul <a href=\"/index.php/Sorcerer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sorcerer\">sorcerer</a>, lest your children and your children's children be cursed forever-more.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the hunchbacked septon</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Every word was <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a>. Even so, it was a shock to see him here, with holes where his eyes had been.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Dunk</b>: Bad business, cutting off the heads of <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septons</a>. All he did was talk. Words are wind.<br />\n<b>Egg</b>: Some words are wind, ser. Some are <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Egg</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Egg</b>: He might have been a <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septon</a>, but he was preaching lies, ser. The drought wasn't Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodraven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloodraven\">Bloodraven</a>'s fault, nor the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Spring_Sickness\" title=\"Great Spring Sickness\">Great Spring Sickness</a> either.<br />\n<b>Dunk</b>: Might be that's so, but if we start cutting off the heads of all the fools and liars, half the towns in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> will be empty.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Egg</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hunchbacked_septon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.8</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404015357\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.082 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.281 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 873/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10841/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 10574/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3058/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3086/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.75 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  262.988      1 -total\n 92.99%  244.557      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 92.50%  243.266      1 Template:Infobox\n  8.99%   23.639     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.33%   11.378      9 Template:Ref\n  4.12%   10.827      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.91%    7.641      2 Template:Date\n  2.07%    5.443      9 Template:Ref/core\n  1.77%    4.663      4 Template:Quote\n  0.86%    2.261      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache wit